  <p id="WiuYfi">Ford’s electric future is being paid for by giant, gas-guzzling trucks and SUVs. </p>
<p id="DUnDpA">That fact came into stark relief this week during the company’s <a href="https://s201.q4cdn.com/693218008/files/doc_financials/2023/q2/Ford-Q2-2023-Corporate-Earnings-Presentation.pdf">second quarter earnings report</a>, in which the Blue Oval reported losing $1.1 billion before interest and taxes on its EV business, more than twice as much it lost over the same period last year. </p>
<p id="5V6l10">Compare that to Ford’s profits in the sale of gas and hybrid trucks and SUVs: $2.3 billion before interest and taxes. Commercial vehicle sales also posted a healthy profit of $2.4 billion for the quarter. </p>
